CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, November 15, 1938, pg. 16, reads: "And the bride, Mrs. Adelaide Lewis Scott, was 'at home.'  Fashionables of Pittsburgh were in evidence to greet a brand new bride, in lower left photo.  Mrs. Granville Woodson, Mrs. Ira Lewis and Mrs. Herman Scott (the bride).  Mrs. Lewis is the mother of both of the young matrons.
TitMainTitle: Jayne Lewis Woodson, Harriet Lewis, and Adelaide Lewis Scott posed in living room
